# Spring Boot Ultimate Production Rules - Database Performance (10 Rules)

1. Prevent N+1 queries by default using fetch planning (`JOIN FETCH`, entity graphs, batch fetch).
2. Paginate all potentially large result sets; never return unbounded collections.
3. Use covering indexes for frequent filter, sort, and join columns.
4. Prefer projection/DTO queries for read-heavy endpoints over full entity loading.
5. Avoid loading large object graphs into memory; fetch only required fields.
6. Profile slow queries with `EXPLAIN ANALYZE` and tune SQL before scaling hardware.
7. Keep transactions and result sets small to reduce lock contention.
8. Use connection pooling with bounded pool size and sane timeout configuration.
9. Optimize schema and indexes with real production-like data distributions.
10. Introduce Redis caching only for measured hotspots with defined TTL and invalidation strategy.
